== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[factiosus]]'' "divisive; inclined to separate"; derivative of ''[[factionem]]''

=== Adjective ===
'''factious'''
# of, pretaining to or caused by [[faction]]s
# given to or characterized by [[discordance]] or [[insubordination]]

=== Noun ===
'''factiousness'''
# the state of being factious

=== Adverb ===
'''factiously'''
# in a factious manner